RACE.RACE_TEXT: HORSESHOE INDIANAPOLIS RACE 1 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR THREE YEARS OLD OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 30, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since September 30 Allowed 3 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOB SECURITY settled off the early pace while moving from the inside to the three path down the backstretch, bid three wide into the far turn, dueled with the runner-up through the turn and into the lane, was still on near even terms approaching the sixteenth pole then inched clear late. GET THROUGH vied from the outset while in the three path, was joined by the winner to make it a trio into the far turn, continued to duel with the winner through the lane and just gave way late. JOHNNY'S MOMENT chased the pace from the two or three path through the turn and into the lane and finished evenly. WEEKEND IN COURT was in the two path while near the back down the backstretch, continued near the back into the lane and passed a tiring rival through the final eighth. SUBURBAN PRINCE vied for the lead two wide into the far turn and gave way. GIVE GOD PRAISE was in the three path throughout and steadily lost ground at each call.

EMPIRES PRINCESS saved ground through the turn while trailing the field, guided to the four path for the drive, steadied and altered in when leader drifted into her path, continued with good energy near the inside and missed. STAGE BELL raced in the three path through the turn when near the back, came into the lane from the four path and was gaining to the end. ARMY GIRL vied for the lead along the inside with two others into the lane, lost contact with the top one, was steadied when another came over nearing the eighth pole and was not a threat thereafter. FLYIN BESSIE vied for the lead from between rivals through the turn into the lane then could not keep up while drifting to the rail. SIMPLY COMPLICATED chased the pace from the five path through the turn, came into the lane from the seven path and tired. LITTLE HOT MESS pressed the pace four wide into the turn, taken off the duelers through the turn while still in the four to the three path and was empty turning into the lane. AFTER AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF #4 EMPIRE PRINCESS, #5 ICICLES WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST (1ST) AND PLACED SECOND (2ND) FOR INTERFERENCE NEAR THE SIXTEENTH POLE.
